          "date": "2014-04-24 17:15:40.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-793 ptlrpc: allow client to reconnect with RPC in progress",
        "message": "LU-793 ptlrpc: allow client to reconnect with RPC in progress\n\nSince not letting clients with pending RPCs to reconnect caused a lot\nof problems, this patch allows such a reconnection and would only\nrefuse to process requests with the same xids that are already being\nprocessed.\n\nBulk requests are aborted upon reconnection by comparing connection\ncount of request and export.\n\nLustre-commit: da6a28fc59a70226dd89bac95880f7791f1db075\nLustre-change: http://review.whamcloud.com/4960\n\nalso includes related change:\nLustre-commit: 50efebe70d503cf0b51be539447de71ad982787e\nLustre-change: http://review.whamcloud.com/8842\n\nSigned-off-by: Mikhail Pershin <mike.pershin@intel.com>\nSigned-off-by: Bob Glossman <bob.glossman@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Johann Lombardi <johann.lombardi@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Alexander Boyko <alexander_boyko@xyratex.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I4242db9fee88f4adbe23a593c3331bf7433da9a6\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_4"
    }
